Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Pat @sirloin steak{14%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Let sit at room temperature until ready to cook.

Cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{16%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, half the @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

> For 4 servings, toss potatoes with all the Fry Seasoning; spread out across entire sheet. Roast, tossing halfway through, 20-25 minutes total.

While potatoes roast, halve, peel, and dice @shallot{1}. Trim, peel, and halve @carrots{6%ounce} lengthwise, then cut into green-bean-sized pieces; toss in a #medium bowl{} with @green beans{6%ounce}, a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, salt, and pepper. Once potatoes have roasted 5 minutes, add carrots and green beans to empty side. (For 4, add to a second baking sheet.) Roast until potatoes are crispy and veggies are tender, ~{15-20%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, melt ½ TBSP @butter{3%tablespoon} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add @almonds{½%ounce}; cook, stirring, ~{2%minutes}. Add @sugar{¼%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{}. Cook until toasted, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan. In a second medium bowl, combine @beef stock concentrate{1}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, and ¼ cup water (⅓ cup for 4).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook until a crust forms on first side, ~{3-6%minutes}. Flip steak and reduce heat to medium. Add @Herbes de Provence{1/2%teaspoon} and 1 TBSP butter. Continue cooking steak to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

> For 4 servings; use more Herbes de Provence.

Melt ½ TBSP butter in same pan over medium heat. Add shallot; cook ~{1%minute}. Add sauce; reduce heat to low. Add any resting juices from steak. Cook until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove pan from heat. Stir in @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and 1 TBSP butter. Slice steak against the grain. Divide steak, potatoes, and veggies between plates. Top steak with sauce. Top veggies with almonds and serve.